  "prompt": "What are some reviews of the Sony Xperia C4?",
  "response": "The Sony Xperia C4 was released back in 2015, so reviews are going to be relatively old. However, here's a summary of common points from reviews at the time:\n\n**Common Positives:**\n\n*   **Excellent Front-Facing Camera:** This was the C4's main selling point. Reviewers praised its 5MP front-facing camera with a wide-angle lens and LED flash for taking great selfies, even in low light.\n*   **Decent Display:** The 5.5-inch Full HD display was generally well-received for its sharpness and color accuracy.\n*   **Smooth Performance:** The MediaTek MT6752 octa-core processor provided a relatively smooth user experience for everyday tasks and moderate gaming.\n*   **Good Battery Life:** Many reviews mentioned the C4's solid battery life, allowing for a full day of use on a single charge.\n*   **Expandable Storage:** The microSD card slot allowed users to expand the internal storage, which was a welcome feature.\n*   **Lightweight Design:** Compared to other 5.5-inch smartphones, the C4 was considered relatively lightweight.\n\n**Common Negatives:**\n\n*   **Plastic Build:** The C4's plastic build felt a bit cheap compared to some of its competitors.\n*   **Rear Camera Performance:** While the front camera excelled, the 13MP rear camera was considered average and struggled in low-light conditions.\n*   **Sony's UI and Bloatware:** Some reviewers criticized Sony's custom UI and the pre-installed bloatware.\n*   **Availability and Price:** Depending on the region, the C4's availability was limited, and its price was considered a bit high compared to similar phones with better specs.\n*   **Speaker Quality:** The speaker quality was often described as mediocre.\n*   **Limited Software Updates:** Given its age, the phone has long ceased to receive software updates, posing a security and compatibility risk.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nThe Sony Xperia C4 was a decent mid-range smartphone in its time, primarily known for its excellent front-facing camera. However, its plastic build, average rear camera, and software limitations were drawbacks. Today, given its age and lack of updates, it's not recommended to purchase this phone unless it is for a very specific purpose and at a very low price.\n\nTo find specific reviews, you can search for \"Sony Xperia C4 review\" on Google or YouTube. You'll find reviews from sites like:\n\n*   GSMArena\n*   TechRadar\n*   Android Authority\n\nKeep in mind the reviews will be from 2015, so consider the context of the time. You will be far better off looking at buying a modern smartphone that is supported with security updates and up-to-date hardware.\n",
